author: Lexie Jeuniewic
title: Two teen boys killed walking from party in NT - 9news.com.au
text:
Two teen boys killed walking from party in NT By Lexie Jeuniewic Two teenage boys have died after being struck by a car in the Northern Territory. (9NEWS) 
Two teenage boys have died after being hit by a car as they returned from a party in Coolalinga, in the Northern Territory, last night. The crash occurred about 2.30am. (9NEWS) Images show significant damage to the white vehicle. (9NEWS) 
The 15-year-olds were struck as they walked home on the Stuart Highway, between the Arnhem Highway and Bees Creek Road, about 2.30am, police said. 
9NEWS understands they were hit by a car being driven by another party guest. Investigations are ongoing. (9NEWS) Police at the scene on the Stuart Highway. (9NEWS)
